cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.HC 

This paper is about dialog policy learning in task-oriented dialog systems, which falls under the category of natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses Reinforcement Learning and Adversarial Inverse Reinforcement Learning, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also focuses on improving task success in dialog systems, which is relevant to the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SD) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
